graph_title: Students graduated in master and special studies by type of education
indicator_name: Students graduated in master and special studies by type of education
title: Untitled
national_indicator_description: Master of science is a person who has completed postgraduate studies and defended the master’s thesis. Master is a person who has completed an study of the second cycle, lasting a year or two, valued at 60 ECTS credits or 120 ECTS credits, the total of points of the first and of the second cycle of studies equals 300 ECTS credits. Specialist is a person who has completed specialist studies and defended the specialist’s thesis.
